# Changelog entries

When shipping user-visible changes, append bilingual items to **`src/data/versionUpdates.ts`**.

## Active date

- Use **`CURRENT_CHANGELOG_DATE`** (`2026-06-20` as of now) for all new items.
- Append to the **first raw entry** with that `date` (id `2026-06-20-summary`).
- Do **not** create a new dated entry for each small change; add groups/items under the active day.
- Same-day multiple raw entries are merged at runtime—prefer one raw block per day.

## Item format

- Each item: `{ zh: '…', en: '…' }`
- Group related items under `groups[].title` (zh/en).
- Keep ids stable; bump `CURRENT_CHANGELOG_DATE` only when the user asks to roll to a new day.
- The updates prompt uses **`getLatestUpdatePromptKey()`** (id + content fingerprint). Appending items to the active day re-triggers the prompt until dismissed again; same content after dismiss does not re-show until the next edit or reset.

## After edits

Run `npm run build:only` (see build-after-changes rule).
